name: B&B interattivo - Naples'Secrets - Stanza Vulcania
description:
Naples' Secrets is the first interactive B&B that offers its guests an unforgettable experience.

You will discover a city rich in history and mysteries thanks to interactive walls, themed rooms and augmented reality.

Located in the heart of the historic center between P. Dante, P. del GesÃ¹ and Via Toledo.

We offer more than 100 classic itineraries and alternative experiences to choose and book directly from the house.
In the interactive room see videos and download pdf guides to take with you around!
neighborhood_overview:
Located in the "San Giuseppe" district, B&B Nples' Secrets is located in the heart of the historic center of Naples. In the immediate vicinity of Piazza Dante, Piazza del GesÃ¹, Spaccanapoli, the Cloister of Santa Chiara and Via Toledo. In a diameter of 700 meters you will find all the most important attractions and museums such as the Sansevero Chapel, the underground Naples and San Gregorio Armeno.
The apartment is located in a building of the late 1800s, on the pedestrian island of the ancient historic center where the Greeks founded the city and where the urban design has remained the same. You will walk among the characteristic Decumani of ancient Neapolis full of shops of all kinds, bars, restaurants, crafts, souvenirs, musicians and street artists. Walking on Via Toledo, a very long street excellent for shopping, you will find the famous Spanish Quarters, full of life until late at night and at the end of the street the beautiful Royal Palace in Piazza del Plebiscito.

Among the historical sites and interest, it is a must to count: the tomb of Virgilio and Giacomo Leopardi whose remains now rest in Piedigrotta, the Roman thermal baths located in Via Terracina and rarely visitable, the 1789 Piperno stele still visible right in Piazza Pilastri which testifies to the establishment by King Ferdiando IV of a sanitary blocking place for wagons and animals used in the hemp and linen maceration in the Lake Agnano area of Lake Agnano.

Fuorigrotta is home to the main Neapolitan sports facilities including: Stadio San Paolo, Pala Barbuto and Piscina Felice Scandone, the shooting range.

name: Wonderful Italy | Casa di Cami
description: Elegant, finely furnished apartment in the Rione Alto area, in the Vomero district.
neighborhood_overview:
"When you go to Naples you cry twice: when you arrive and when you leave," they say. Naples is a unique city to be experienced by walking through the alleys, smelling the aroma of gastronomic delicacies in the air and admiring its rich artistic and monumental heritage.
Naples is the origin of a distinctive culinary tradition for its famous Neapolitan pizza, and the art of its pizza makers has been declared an intangible heritage of humanity by Unesco.
As you stroll through Spaccanapoli, the street that cuts the city in half, you pass through its thousand-year history thanks to the presence of ancient palaces and churches, such as the Duomo di Napoli and the Maschio Angioino. If there is a symbolic place in Naples, this is Piazza del Plebiscito, now a symbol of the new "Neapolitan Renaissance" where tourists come to admire its grandeur and two jewels: the neoclassical colonnade of the church of San Francesco di Paola and the Royal Palace.
